Usage: skillctl install <name>[@<version>] [flags]

Pulls a skill bundle from the registry, runs the SPEC-0188 §7 verifier,
and atomically installs it under ~/.claude/skills/<name>/. Refuses if any
trust-chain step fails.

<version> may be a human version string (e.g. 1.0.0) or a digest pin
(sha256:<hex>). Omit to install the newest admitted version.

Numbered exit codes (SPEC-0188 §11):
   0  ok
   1  generic error
   2  usage / flag error
  10  digest mismatch
  11  author signature invalid
  12  registry not in trust roots
  13  governance below minimum
  14  depends_on unsatisfied
  15  blob missing
  16  tenant blocked (CISO console verdict)
  -allow-yellow
    	Lower the gate from green to yellow for this install (audited).
  -governance-min string
    	Override the trust-root's governance_minimum (green | yellow). Empty = use trust-root.
  -home string
    	Override the install root (advanced; defaults to $HOME).
  -ignore-deps
    	Skip depends_on resolution (audited).
  -registry string
    	Registry base URL. Required only when trust-roots has multiple registries pinned.
  -tenant string
    	Pin this install to a tenant scope (SPEC-0188 §7 step 5.5). Overrides trust-roots tenant_scope. Empty = use trust-roots value or run untenanted.
  -timeout duration
    	HTTP timeout for registry calls. (default 30s)
  -verbose
    	Print structured per-step log lines to stderr.
